  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Sereja have **N** points, with coordinates **(1, 0), (2, 0), ..., (N, 0)**. Every point has a color, point with coordinate **(i, 0)** has color **A[i]**.\n\nSereja have painted arcs between every pair of points with same color. Formally Sereja painted arc between points **(i, 0)** and **(j, 0)** if **A[i] = A[j]** and **i != j**, such arc has color **A[i]**. All the arcs are painted such way that they will reside along the positive quadrant.\n\nNow Sereja wants to know how many pairs of arc with different color intersect?",
    "constraints": [
      "**1** ≤ **N** ≤ **100000**",
      "**1** ≤ **A[i]** ≤ **100000**",
      "&nbsp;",
      "Example**Input:**",
      "4",
      "1 2 1 2",
      "**Output:**",
      "1"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "&nbsp;First line contain integer **N**. Next line contain integers **A[1], A[2], ..., A[N]**.",
    "outputFormat": "&nbsp;In single line output answer modulo **1000000007 (10^9 + 7)**.&nbsp;",
